CogniTech Corporation is a small privately held company located in Salt
Lake City, Utah.  After finishing my Ph.D. in Computer Science and
serving as a Research Instructor at the University of Utah, I founded
CogniTech in 1996.  We are seeking to hire one full-time software
engineer to begin employment in the end of April or early May, 2000.
The position will initially focus on the design and development of a
distributed web framework and interface to simulations and software
algorithms for pattern recognition and image recognition.

Benefits of working at CogniTech:
* challenging, flexible, and team-based work environment
* competitive salary and benefits.

CogniTech specializes in the following technologies:
*  design (Rational Rose/UML modeling, data modeling)
*  computer languages (Java, C/C++, Visual Basic, Delphi)
*  dynamic web site creation (servlets, JSP, XML/XSL, ASP, DHTML,
JavaScript)
*  distributed objects (CORBA, EJB, DCOM/ActiveX)
*  relational databases (SQL, JDBC) and
*  application servers.

Requirements for this Position:
1. U.S. citizenship (or a green card)
2. Ability to
   a. work full-time or
   b. be a part-time M.S. or Ph.D. student and work at least 30 hours
per week
3. Minimum of B.S. in Computer Science or related field
4. Two years of professional experience in Java and distributed objects
is desired, but not necessary.

